                                 Testimonies
                                 [gray.gif]

   On July 22, 1997, the House of Representatives Committee on the
   Judiciary Subcommittee on the Constitution held a hearing on H.J. Res.
   78, the Religious Freedom Amendment. For a full list of witnesses and
   their testimonies, visit the Judiciary Committee's witness list for the
   RFA hearing.

   Below, you can read the testimony of the two principle sponsors of the
   Religious Freedom Amendment, Congressman Istook and Congressman Bishop.

     7/22/97 Congressman Istook's Testimony

     7/22/97 Congressman Bishop's Testimony

